reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works Great and easy install
reviews.reviewText: I put this in a Dell computer (older) I added a external PSU, because the stock Dell PSU was only 250 watts and I needed more wattage to run a new graphics card, it required minimum 400 watts. This module triggers the secondary PSU to start at the same time as the Dell PSU inside the desktop. From my research its really important to make sure if you run a 2nd PSU that they both start at the exact time. This module does exactly that. I've had it for about 4 months now and no problems. Great solution if you want to have a 2nd PSU. Now all I have to do is hit the (ON) button and they both start up. The same when shutting down the desktop, both PSU's stop at the same time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quick and easy install, works perfectly.
reviews.reviewText: Some people ask why I don't simply jump the pins on the secondary power supply. It's not because I am too lazy to turn on the other power supply seperately. It is because in the event the computer shuts down on its own, which it has a few times, I want all the power supplies in my rig to also turn off and quit powering the GPUs on secondary power supplies. This device does that.
